1)The bandwidth of wifi is 40 MHz.
2)The channels 1-11 are available.
3)People commonly use 1, 6, or 11 because they overlap the least.
4)Wired Equivelent Privacy(WEP),Wifi Protected Access(WPA),Wired Protected Access 2(WPA2).
The difference is the amount of security each one provides.
5)WPA2 is the most secure and WEP is the least.
6)AirSnort is a program to decrypt WEP encryption keys.
7)Kismet is an intrusion detection system.
8)Karma is is a portable box of wifi.
